cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The use of interference decoding and multiple description coding techniques suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) and cs.SI (social and information networks). The mention of MISO BC suggests a possible categorization under cs.MM (multimedia), while the use of encoding and decoding techniques may also suggest a categorization under cs.CC (computational complexity).
